         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/8/82, ¶  ¶ Best thanks, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  for the sending of Phyllachnes &amp;c, also for the sketch of flower of Epiblema. ¶  Could you not spare  ¶ even one ¶  flower of the plant for me, to disse...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.08.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26/8/82,</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> for the sending of <name key="Phyllachnes">Phyllachnes</name> &amp;c, also for the sketch of flower of <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sketch not found.</p>
               </note> Could you not spare <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">even one</hi>
               </seg> flower of the plant for me, to dissect and carefully compare? Is it gone to England, to be worked out? Any how the plant there <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">interests me much</hi>
               </seg> in connection with Australian vegetation.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">In Buchanan (1882), pp. 356-7, an orchid collected by H. L. T. Travers was identified as the Australian </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name> grandiflorum</seg>
                     <seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith a proofsheet of the geographic &amp; chronologic census of all Australian species of plants, of which work the dicotyledoneae will appear in 1882.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B83.03.04.</p>
               </note> Can you not do something similar for the N.Z. setting out the provinces as I have done the colonies. I would gladly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">help you</hi>
               </seg> in the chronologic data.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">If you asked Mr Travers, I feel sure he would let me have one of the flowers of his <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>, and if in comparison I should find any distinctions, it could be named after that Gentleman.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">No </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> named for Travers has been found (IPNI accessed 20 March 2022).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Phyllachnes">Phyllachnes</name>
            </p>
